                  <persName id="t18280410-231-person1297">
                  WILLIAM 
                  NEWMAN
               <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1297" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1297" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1297" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Thomas Harland, a <rs id="t18280410-231-viclabel1235" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-231-victim1296 t18280410-231-viclabel1235"></join>, of <placeName id="t18280410-231-crimeloc1236">St. John-street, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-231-crimeloc1236" type="placeName" value="St. John-street, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-231-crimeloc1236" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-231-off1233 t18280410-231-crimeloc1236"></join>. On the 15th of March, about four o'clock in the afternoon, my boy was going out to take some cheese, and gave me information; I went to the door, and saw the prisoner with this cheese, going from the shop; the boy took hold of him, and brought him back; we took it from him - he said he would never do the like again. Mr. Harland let him go, and in about half an hour he returned, and took another piece out of the window; Hocker brought him back, and I took it from under his coat - he was a little in liquor.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-231-person1298">
                  SAMUEL 
                  HOCKER
               <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1298" type="surname" value="HOCKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1298" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1298" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a butcher, and live opposite the prosecutor. On Saturday afternoon I was at my door, and saw the prisoner brought back with the cheese; they pardoned him, and he left; but in about twenty minutes I saw him return, and go staggering up to the shop; he took this piece of cheese with a ticket on it - he deliberately took the ticket off, and put the cheese under his arm; I crossed over, collared him, and took him back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-231-person1299">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18280410-231-person1299" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
